text: River East Center is a Chicago skyscraper. It is a part of the larger River East complex. The tower, containing 620 condominium units, is 644 feet (196 m) tall with 58 floors, and was completed in 2001. ==Related pages== *List of tallest buildings in the United States *List of tallest buildings in Chicago ==Other websites== *Emporis listing *Archive of Official Website Category:Skyscrapers in Chicago Category:2001 establishments in the United States Category:2000s establishments in Illinois
